# API and Auth Risk Checks

- Validate request inputs before business logic and external calls.
- Avoid leaking internals in errors; sanitize messages and logs.
- Enforce auth/session/token checks explicitly for protected routes.
- Add or update tests for success path, failure path, and abuse edge cases.
- For third-party APIs, include timeout/fallback/error-path handling.

## Quick pass/fail check

- [ ] Input validation exists for new/changed entry points
- [ ] Auth boundaries are explicit and tested
- [ ] Errors and logs avoid sensitive leakage
